</taxonomicName>
; (4) 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3D52FB0C3A9FFAD1" authorityName="Darby" authorityYear="1965" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macrocypris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapeloensis">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3D52FB0C3A9FFAD1" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. sapeloensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3BD6FB2E3D4DFAD1" authorityName="Jellinek &amp; Swanson" authorityYear="2003" box="[999,1143,1269,1290]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonneae">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3BD6FB2E3D4DFAD1" box="[999,1143,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. sonneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
present a more evenly rounded dorsal margin than 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3CA8FACF3C05FAF3" authorityName="Brandão" authorityYear="2010" box="[1177,1343,1299,1321]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alanlordi">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3CA8FACF3C05FAF3" box="[1177,1343,1299,1321]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. alanlordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with more sinuous outline); (5) 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3C56FAE83DD1FA9C" authorityName="Jellinek &amp; Swanson" authorityYear="2003" box="[1127,1259,1330,1352]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thiedei">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3C56FAE83DD1FA9C" box="[1127,1259,1330,1352]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. thiedei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more subtriangular than 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3BD6FA8A3DBCFABE" authorityName="Brandão" authorityYear="2010" box="[999,1158,1360,1382]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alanlordi">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3BD6FA8A3DBCFABE" box="[999,1158,1360,1382]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. alanlordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and (6) 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3CC7FA8A3CB7FABE" authorityName="Maddocks" authorityYear="1990" box="[1270,1421,1360,1382]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steinecki">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3CC7FA8A3CB7FABE" box="[1270,1421,1360,1382]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. steinecki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a conspicuously more sinuate outline, and more acute posterior angle. The female valve outline of 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3B7DFA763ACBFA1A" authority="Brandão, 2010" authorityName="Brandão" authorityYear="2010" box="[844,1009,1452,1474]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alanlordi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3B7DFA763ACBFA1A" box="[844,1009,1452,1474]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. alanlordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="25D35786FFCCEB0B3C32FA763D58FA19" box="[1027,1122,1453,1474]" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3D52FA763A44FA3A" authorityName="Maddocks" authorityYear="1990" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoena">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3D52FA763A44FA3A" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. amoena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3BA9FA173D11FA3B" authorityName="Maddocks" authorityYear="1990" box="[920,1067,1483,1505]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adrecta">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3BA9FA173D11FA3B" box="[920,1067,1483,1505]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. adrecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3CB3FA173C77FA3B" authorityName="Hulings" authorityYear="1967" box="[1154,1357,1483,1505]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macrocypris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bathyalensis">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3CB3FA173C77FA3B" box="[1154,1357,1483,1505]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. bathyalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these three species present a Zenker’s organ with a medium-sized terminal bulb, instead of a very large one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C2B36EFFFCCEB0B3B0EF99D3DC0F8B5" blockId="32.[806,1422,657,1903]" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3B0EF99D3D24F981" authorityName="Maddocks" authorityYear="1990" box="[831,1054,1605,1627]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adrecta">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3B0EF99D3D24F981" box="[831,1054,1605,1627]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Macropyxis adrecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seams to be the closest species to 
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3B77F9BE3ADEF9A2" authorityName="Brandão" authorityYear="2010" box="[838,996,1636,1658]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alanlordi">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3B77F9BE3ADEF9A2" box="[838,996,1636,1658]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. alanlordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of similarities in the hemipenis (outline and copulatory process) and valve outline (especially in females), however both species differ, as cited above, in the terminal bulb of the Zenker’s organ. The occurrence of these species in abyssal depths of the SO (
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3C44F9253C22F8C9" authorityName="Brandão" authorityYear="2010" box="[1141,1304,1789,1811]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alanlordi">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3C44F9253C22F8C9" box="[1141,1304,1789,1811]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. alanlordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the Southern Atlantic (
<taxonomicName id="CB944D6CFFCCEB0B3C35F8C73DB6F8EA" authorityName="Maddocks" authorityYear="1990" box="[1028,1164,1820,1841]" class="Ostracoda" family="Macrocyprididae" genus="Macropyxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="32" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adrecta">
<emphasis id="3EE0EAFDFFCCEB0B3C35F8C73DB6F8EA" box="[1028,1164,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="599">Mx. adrecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is possibly the result of dispersion facilitated by the northward flow of the bottom water masses formed in the SO.
</paragraph>
